This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it discusses the use of software-defined networks (SDNs) for traffic engineering. It may also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it addresses the challenge of minimizing disruptions during network updates. Additionally, it could be categorized under the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it involves the coordination of network updates and the optimization of network performance. Finally, it may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category as it discusses the implementation of a Time4-enabled OpenFlow prototype.
